Key Match Events: Cenk Tosun scored a stoppage-time winner for Turkey
Turkey's win eliminates Czech Republic from the Euro 2024 knockout round
Post-Match Reflections: Cenk Tosun expressed his delight with his goal
Turkey's captain Tomas Soucek expressed disappointment at the loss
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was marked by a flare-up between players and substitutes after the final whistle
Romanian referee Istvan Kovacs showed 18 yellow cards and sent off Czech midfielder Antonin Barak
Others: The Czech Republic was without star player Patrik Schick due to a calf muscle injury
